is very industrious about it.  But I have to disapprove of what she is doing, and I told her as much.  I don't think it's honorable.  I won't buy from her, and I won't sell to her either, unless I think it's for her actual use.  I don't think I'll have to worry about selling to her at all anymore, regardless.<br><br>What I would like to ask people is if they think this activity is honorable.  Is this a reasonable trade activity?  I know she is buying items from high level people who are giving her a break because she is still quite a low level, and then selling them to other people for every copper she can squeeze.  I get particularly offended when she tries to resell jeweler I have made, or might have made, at more than I sell it for.  I offer jewelery at the best prices I can (on gold now, and selling that at a loss, technically, because I am still skilling up on it) and I don't why someone else should gouge people for it and make a profit off my work just because I try to give reasonable prices.<br><br>Here is another example.  Crude Steins are a hot ticket item on FV.  I've been wanting one for ages.  The other day Stormwynd sold me one for 70 plat, giving me a deal because I wasn't very liquid at all.  I could probably sell it for more with little trouble.  But aside from the fact that I am using it anyway, I feel that would be an abuse of his generosity.<br><br>I want people's opinions on this subject, because I'm not sure now where I should stand.  If people are firming against this kind of &quot;ninja trading&quot; (just invented that term) I am fully prepared to start and update a public list any time I catch people at this.  If not, I'll just keep my notes to myself and have a personal little &quot;no buy, no sell&quot; list.  Please offer feedback.<br><br>Valquiss Silverpalm<br><br>P.S. If the elf in question should read this, and you know who you are, stop even trying to affect my reputation.  Even when I'm not around to defend myself, my reputation is far better than yours, and you'll only hurt yourself by setting yourself up against me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usliver123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sliver123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/01 5:49:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying Low, Selling High</span><hr size=1> Well, I dunno. If people are willing to sell to her, and others are willing to buy from her, then its just enterprise. Enterpirse can be a dirty word, but really I think all this does is serve up a wake up to higher level players to be wary of who they help out. Personally I give most of my lower end stuff away, because I am in a guild that looks after its members pretty well. If someone sells this gear for their pony fund and doesn't use it, so be it ... I parted with it by choice, it's their stuff now. They can do what they like. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucasbenlightfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casben Lightfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/01 8:25:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying Low, Selling High</span><hr size=1> On my old server, the &quot;auction&quot; zone was crawling with these types of people though.  All they would do is buy and sell items, all day long.  They would set the prices and wouldn't budge... but if you tried to sell an item you had, they would undercut you or offer much less.  I tried doing this every once in a while, but it got very boring, and it's not exactly nice.  I was also a rogue, so it was in my nature to fence smuggled goods at times.  I don't think I've ever sold anything on Firiona Vie, but I do barter and exchange services for services.<br><br>Perhaps they are enterprizing, or being a crafty tradesman.  But most of the time they are taking advantage of the kindness of others, and then selling the item to those who don't care how much it costs. <br><br>On Firiona Vie I'm content with gathering my own items, crafting my own goods, and staying out of the haggling.  The less looted items are bought and sold, the less &quot;farming&quot; occurs.  Tradesmens' wares are of course a different story.<br><br>To each his own.<br> <p><b><i>Casben Lightfoot</i></b>, Grumpy ol' Rake from Tunare<br><b><i>Sabbik Silvertongue</i></b>, cleric of the Tinker's Pride</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/01 9:03:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying Low, Selling High</span><hr size=1> If I was you, I would just post her name all over the place.  On FV there isn't as much money as other servers and most people don't have very much to spend so you should give her name out just for consumer protection. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/01 10:21:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying Low, Selling High</span><hr size=1> &lt;shrug&gt;<br>Some folks get off on that, it's supply and demand. Face it folks want items, and after a hard day at the frost giant, or any other nice cash dropping mod they're more than happy to pay a little extra for them. Prices are only as high as folks are willing to pay. As to reselling, well in jewlery's case your prices are pretty defined, everyone knows what those bars and gems cost. &lt;with the exeption of Diamond/Blue Diamond stuff&gt; I'm really not bothered by foks sitting around trying to make a profit as a merchant, I'd recommend a different server as this one doesn't have nearly the cash, bank space, or set area for auction. If they want to do it that badly they will, even if it means buying another account strictly for a sale's person that gets wiped every week for a new name.<br><br>Anyway if she is buying stuff at cost then reselling it higher. Either ask her for a cut, or riase your prices to her so that you can recoup. As the number of 250 jewlers increases you'll notice that most guilds will have one that makes jewlery at cost for there members.<br><br>So to wrap this up, I'm not suprised that those folk are about, they are what makes a servers economy though. I'm sorry that your trust was broken.<br><br>my 2cp not that they are worth any thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=morgrist>Morgrist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/01 12:11:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> If your jewelcrafting's been resold at a profit....</span><hr size=1> ...then ya set yer price lower than ya need it t'be.<br> <br>Stop givin her t'profit and make it yerself!<br> <br>-Morgrist Vanadil (League of Shadows)<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/01 3:27:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying Low, Selling High</span><hr size=1> Valquiss:<br><br>First, let me say that of all the people I've met on this server, your name is the most respected in my mind.  I've always felt that the idea of the Traders Union is a fantastic one, and you seem to me to be the epitome of a fair salesman.<br><br>That said, I'm a little confused about how this unnamed person (I think I know who she might be--there's someone who's been undercutting my prices on Raw Silk fairly consistently, sellling it for just barely over what I can sell it back to NPC Merchants for) is making a profit off of jewellry you've made for her, unless you sold her the jewellry at a discount in the first place.<br><br>It sounds like, to me, that what she's done is set up shop and is charging lower prices than you are in order to drum up business.  That's free market capitalism for you.  Either you lower your prices to compete with her, or you rely on your reputation and clout to maintain your prices (and probably lose some customers to her).<br><br>If you spent some time selling at just above cost, turning only a slight profit, you might be able to undercut her efforts.  But it sounds to me like this is more of a trade war than something unethical.<br><br>Lasgalen, Sixteenth Autumn Initiate of Tunare, Tailor/Potter/Blacksmith (and I might open a Grocery Store, with the amount of veggies and fruits I lug around with me) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A> at: 12/16/01 3:33:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/01 4:29:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying Low, Selling High</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry, I should have been more specific.  In fact, she is selling at quite a bit more than I do, but doing it when I'm not there.  The trade-crafted items are a small part of this issue, it's just what rankles me the most personally.  It's more a question of found items which have less of a fixed price.  She's buying them cheaply when she can, off people who take pity on a lower-leveled character, then selling them for every coin she can get later on.  I still don't know how I should feel about it.  More opinions are sought after.<br><br>Valquiss <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vallya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/01 4:39:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying Low, Selling High</span><hr size=1> I would not worry about a person marking your merchandise up.  On FV a person has to auction around to get an item sold. It takes time and effort. We can't just pop into the East Commons like we did in the old world. If this person were not going to the trouble of auctioning the goods in more or different places than you are, no one would be buying from them. If what is happening bothers you, then the answer is to act as your own distributor. Spend the additional time running around all the town zones auctioning. If you are like me, you'd rather not spend all your time sitting in town auctioning though :-)<br><br>You mentioned attempts to ruin your reputation. If the person is slandering you, that is another matter. I would let anyone who bad mouthed me find a new supplier.<br><br>The vendors who worry me are those who sell merchandise for LESS than my cost. I never expected to get rich in the trades, but breaking even might be nice.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwyrdup.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyrd Up</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/01 9:40:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> well</span><hr size=1> that's capitalism for you.<br><br>It stinks she's abusing her being low level to get items, but it's not that different from the &quot;newbie&quot; going around looking pitiful, so you hand him a few items.. and to see him later with better gear than you do.<br><br>You'll get the repeat business.. she won't.  For me, I'm loving the Trader's Union folks already, they helped me obtain my Trueshot bow for a VERY fair price. *thanks you heartily*<br><br>Kyrial <p>Brandy... the ambrosia of Norrath.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhaqimofsharvahl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haqim of SharVahl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/01 10:05:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't worry too much, resellers at marked up prices won't be able to move too much merchandise here.<br><br>I don't think a blacklist is required, the market will be lean enough as it is. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=brainstalker>Brainstalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/01 12:43:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> What she is doing is fine.  If she is over charging then it will catch up to her and she'll be out of business.<br><br>On the other hand, you should not be selling for a loss (including fails).  Doing so hurts all tradesmen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulammfallaway.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lamm Fallaway</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/01 4:10:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> Sorry but I do find this a bit amusing.  This is a RP preferred server, but if someone wants to be a MERCHANT and buy and sell stuff all day, who cares?  And you may use the argument &quot;well this person wasnt even RPing so they are just a d00d&quot; well I dont know the person so I cant say.<br><br>Guess what?  To make money, merchants HAVE to buy low and sell high.  Think about IC a merchant from Freeport or what not.  They are going to barter. They are going to try to buy as cheaply as possible.  They are going to try to sell as high as possible.  This is what a real and true merchant would do and it's very IC.  Why is this a problem if a person decides they want to play this character?<br><br>There is no &quot;honorable&quot; price to sell stuff at.  In Norrath you are only allowed to sell for what another will pay for the item.  No cant force anyone to buy anything.  If someone doesnt like your prices, they will find someone else to buy from.<br><br><br>quote:<br>&quot;Perhaps they are enterprizing, or being a crafty tradesman. But most of the time they are taking advantage of the kindness of others, and then selling the item to those who don't care how much it costs.&quot;<br><br>Yes this is the very definition of &quot;enterprising and crafty&quot; in regards to being a merchant.  A merchant will use everything they can to give themselves an advantage.<br><br>So, I find it a bit rude that you are slandering this person.  Play the game how you want and let others play the game how they want.  If you feel slanted by this person, then dont sell to them or make it know that you sell lower than them.  But to send them tells in regards to their &quot;ninja trading&quot; (or whatever term you used) is just plain rude. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 352<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/01 5:11:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Well her actions are in character with being a greedy merchant.<br><br>I think I met the lass you are talking about, she haggled over my 100pp price for a stein o maggok, in the end she traded for something my sister wanted worth less but she did want it.<br><br>In the next breath she was auctioning it. Damn I was annoyed by this BUT thats because I do not beleive in greed.<br><br>There are 3 ways I know of to get pp rich in EQ (not sure about smithing and other skills).<br><br>1. Farming<br>2. Jewelry<br>3. Trading<br><br>To be honest I would say that though you might end up with lots of PP you will end up poor in the real wealth of life. But thats just me.<br><br>I tend to buy Hi sell Low (or give away).<br>Do not think I have ever made a proffit on anything ever :-)<br>Sounds like I am an easy mark, maybe I am, but Karma is a powerful thing.<br><br>You think once this person has stiffed a few people that when she