end me a tell in game next time. =)<br><br>Windroll~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/24/01 12:03:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying Low, Selling High</span><hr size=1> Valquiss:<br><br>I think I know exactly who this is.<br><br>If it is, she's my only &quot;disgruntled&quot; customer.  I sold a certain someone, who I now have reason to believe is the same certain someone you're talking about, Raw Silk back when it was still not trivial to me.  I went by the rate the Traders Union person next to me told was the going rate for Raw Silk (1 platinum per AC minus 1 platinum per piece).  I'd sold it at that rate before, and I've sold it at that rate after, with no complaints from anyone about my price.  Sometimes, I offer a &quot;free lunch&quot; with it, sometimes not.  At any rate, she thought the price was fair enough when she bought it from me.<br><br>A few days later, I log on, and this certain high elf sends me a barrage of /tells about how I &quot;ripped her off&quot; and how the next day she'd gotten the rest of her Raw Silk for 5 gold a piece.  I said &quot;Good for you, sounds like you got a deal from that other merchant, and I'm sorry you feel you were ripped off by me but my price is what I understand to be the going rate.&quot;<br><br>I wonder, now, if she got so mad (and apparently remains mad, as she sent me /tells about how I &quot;ripped her off&quot; just yesterday before I put her on /ignore) because she tried to resell my Raw Silk at a higher price.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img sr